-- Turkey's Ziraat Bank applies to watchdog to set up Islamic lender
-- By Ece Toksabay
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 04:37AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 29 (Reuters) - Turkish state-run Ziraat Bank has applied to the country's banking watchdog (BDDK) to establish an Islamic lender, it said in a statement on Friday.

